
Overview of noun splendor

The noun splendor has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (2) luster, lustre, brilliancy, splendor, splendour -- (a quality that outshines the usual)
2. (2) magnificence, brilliance, splendor, splendour, grandeur, grandness -- (the quality of being magnificent or splendid or grand; "for magnificence and personal service there is the Queen's hotel"; "his `Hamlet' lacks the brilliance that one expects"; "it is the university that gives the scene its stately splendor"; "an imaginative mix of old-fashioned grandeur and colorful art"; "advertisers capitalize on the grandness and elegance it brings to their products")
